§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ How does the power set relate to a union? ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation preliminaries ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $E$ denote a set. ⦉

  ‖ Let $𝒜$ denote a set of subsets of the set denoted by $E$. ⦉

  ‖ We define $⋃_{A ∈ 𝒜} A$ to mean $⋃ 𝒜$. ⦉
⦉

§ Basic properties ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Here are some basic interactions between the powerset and
    unions.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will expand on these propositions and
        provide accounts of them. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $\powerset{E} ∪ \powerset{F} ⊂ \powerset{(E ∪ F)}$ ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $⋃_{X ∈ 𝒞} \powerset{X} ⊂ \powerset{(⋃_{X ∈ 𝒞} X)}$ ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $E = ⋃ \powerset{E}$ ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $\powerset{(⋃ E)} ⊃ E$. ⦉
</statement>

‖ Typically $E ≠ \powerset{(⋃ E)}$, in which case $E$ is a
  proper subset. ⦉
